                                                                                                                                    Clooney a messenger of peace

              
	United Nations, Jan. 19 (Reuters): Secretary-general Ban Ki-moon named US actor George Clooney, who has campaigned for refugees in Darfur, as a UN messenger of peace yesterday to promote the world bodys peacekeeping efforts.
    
	Clooney is the ninth UN messenger  people chosen from the fields of art, music, literature and sports who have agreed to help focus attention on the UNs work.
    
	United Nations spokeswoman Michele Montas said Clooney would have a special emphasis on peacekeeping. She said he had been recognised for focusing public attention on crucial international political and social issues.
    
	Clooney, who is currently in Sudan, will receive his designation on January 31 at UN headquarters. 
                                                                                
